-- The modality without the star operation

-- The "linear or affine types" semiring with meet

linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet : Semiring-with-meet
linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet  = record
  { _+_          = _+_
  ; _¬∑_          = _¬∑_
  ; _‚àß_          = _‚àß_
  ; ùüò            = ùüò
  ; ùüô            = ùüô
  ; œâ            = ‚â§œâ
  ; œâ‚â§ùüô          = refl
  ; œâ¬∑+‚â§œâ¬∑ ≥      = Œª {p = p} ‚Üí ‚â§œâ¬∑+‚â§‚â§œâ¬∑ ≥ p
  ; is-ùüò?        = _‚âü ùüò
  ; +-¬∑-Semiring = record
    { isSemiringWithoutAnnihilatingZero = record
      { +-isCommutativeMonoid = record
        { isMonoid = record
          { isSemigroup = record
            { isMagma = record
              { isEquivalence = PE.isEquivalence
              ; ‚àô-cong        = cong‚ÇÇ _+_
              }
            ; assoc = +-assoc
            }
          ; identity =
                (Œª _ ‚Üí refl)
              , comm‚àßidÀ°‚áíid ≥ +-comm (Œª _ ‚Üí refl)
          }
        ; comm = +-comm
        }
      ; *-cong = cong‚ÇÇ _¬∑_
      ; *-assoc = ¬∑-assoc
      ; *-identity =
              ¬∑-identityÀ°
            , comm‚àßidÀ°‚áíid ≥ ¬∑-comm ¬∑-identityÀ°
      ; distrib =
            ¬∑-distribÀ°-+
          , comm‚àßdistrÀ°‚áídistr ≥ ¬∑-comm ¬∑-distribÀ°-+
      }
    ; zero =
          (Œª _ ‚Üí refl)
        , comm‚àßzeÀ°‚áíze ≥ ¬∑-comm (Œª _ ‚Üí refl)
    }
  ; ‚àß-Semilattice = record
    { isBand = record
      { isSemigroup = record
        { isMagma = record
          { isEquivalence = PE.isEquivalence
          ; ‚àô-cong        = cong‚ÇÇ _‚àß_
          }
        ; assoc = ‚àß-assoc
        }
      ; idem = Œª where
          ùüò  ‚Üí refl
          ùüô  ‚Üí refl
          ‚â§ùüô ‚Üí refl
          ‚â§œâ ‚Üí refl

    }
  ; ¬∑-distrib-‚àß =
        ¬∑-distribÀ°-‚àß
      , comm‚àßdistrÀ°‚áídistr ≥ ¬∑-comm ¬∑-distribÀ°-‚àß
  ; +-distrib-‚àß =
        +-distribÀ°-‚àß

  }

-- A star operation for a ModalityWithout‚äõ for Linear-or-affine for
-- which the zero is ùüò, the one is ùüô, addition is _+_, multiplication
-- is _¬∑_, and the meet operation is _‚àß_ has to satisfy the
-- Star-requirements if certain conditions are satisfied.

Star-requirements-required‚Ä≤ :
  (M : Semiring-with-meet) ‚Üí
  Semiring-with-meet.ùüò   M ‚â° ùüò ‚Üí
  Semiring-with-meet.ùüô   M ‚â° ùüô ‚Üí
  Semiring-with-meet._+_ M ‚â° _+_ ‚Üí
  Semiring-with-meet._¬∑_ M ‚â° _¬∑_ ‚Üí
  Semiring-with-meet._‚àß_ M ‚â° _‚àß_ ‚Üí
  (_‚äõ_‚ñ∑_ :
   Linear-or-affine ‚Üí Linear-or-affine ‚Üí Linear-or-affine ‚Üí
   Linear-or-affine) ‚Üí
  (‚àÄ p q r ‚Üí (p ‚äõ q ‚ñ∑ r) ‚â§ q + r ¬∑ (p ‚äõ q ‚ñ∑ r)) ‚Üí
  (‚àÄ p q r ‚Üí (p ‚äõ q ‚ñ∑ r) ‚â§ p) ‚Üí
  (‚àÄ r ‚Üí _¬∑_ SubDistributesOver ≥ (_‚äõ_‚ñ∑ r) by _‚â§_) ‚Üí
  Star-requirements _‚äõ_‚ñ∑_
Star-requirements-required‚Ä≤
  M@record{} refl refl refl refl refl star ‚äõ-ineq‚ÇÅ ‚äõ-ineq‚ÇÇ
  ¬∑-sub-distrib ≥-‚äõ =

  ¬∑-distrib ≥-‚äõ : ‚àÄ r ‚Üí _¬∑_ DistributesOver ≥ (_‚äõ_‚ñ∑ r)

  ‚äõ-distribÀ°-‚àß : ‚àÄ r ‚Üí (_‚äõ_‚ñ∑ r) DistributesOverÀ° _‚àß_

        p ‚àß ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (q ‚àß q‚Ä≤)             ‚â°‚ü® ‚àß-congÀ° (¬∑-distribÀ°-‚àß ‚â§œâ q _) ‚ü©

        ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (p ‚àß q ‚àß q‚Ä≤)             ‚â°‚ü® cong (‚â§œâ ¬∑_) (lemma p _ _) ‚ü©
        ‚â§œâ ¬∑ ((p ‚àß q) ‚àß (p ‚àß q‚Ä≤))     ‚â°‚ü® ¬∑-distribÀ°-‚àß ‚â§œâ (p ‚àß _) _ ‚ü©
        ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (p ‚àß q) ‚àß ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (p ‚àß q‚Ä≤)  ‚àé
    where
    open Tools.Reasoning.PropositionalEquality

    lemma = Œª p q q‚Ä≤ ‚Üí
      p ‚àß (q ‚àß q‚Ä≤)        ‚â°Àò‚ü® cong (_‚àß _) (‚àß-idem p) ‚ü©
      (p ‚àß p) ‚àß (q ‚àß q‚Ä≤)  ‚â°‚ü® ‚àß-assoc p _ _ ‚ü©

      p ‚àß ((q ‚àß p) ‚àß q‚Ä≤)  ‚â°‚ü® cong (p ‚àß_) (‚àß-assoc q _ _) ‚ü©
      p ‚àß (q ‚àß (p ‚àß q‚Ä≤))  ‚â°Àò‚ü® ‚àß-assoc p _ _ ‚ü©
      (p ‚àß q) ‚àß (p ‚àß q‚Ä≤)  ‚àé

  ‚äõ-distrib ≥-‚àß : ‚àÄ r ‚Üí (_‚äõ_‚ñ∑ r) DistributesOver ≥ _‚àß_

      ùüô q p p‚Ä≤ ‚Üí

    where
    open Tools.Reasoning.PropositionalEquality

    lemma = Œª q p p‚Ä≤ ‚Üí
      (p ‚àß p‚Ä≤) ‚àß q        ‚â°‚ü® ‚àß-comm _ q ‚ü©

-- Custom nr functions for the Modality

opaque

  -- A (not very good) nr function based on the natrec-star operator

  -- See Graded.Modality.Instances.Linear-or-affine.Bad for some
  -- examples that illustrate in what sense this nr function is not very
  -- good. The nr function below does not suffer from

  bad-linear-or-affine-has-nr : Has-nr linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet

-- An nr function for Linear-or-affine.
--
-- The value of nr¬†p¬†ùüò¬†z¬†s¬†n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†ùüô, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls, and the
--   argument is used exactly once in the successor case (excluding
--   erased uses):
--
--     f zero    = f_z
--     f (suc m) = f_s m
--
--   Let us use n¬†+¬†z for the zero case, and n¬†+¬†s for the successor
--   case: the result is a conservative approximation of these two
--   values (their meet).
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†ùüò, then there are no (non-erased) recursive
--   calls, and the argument is not used (in non-erased positions) in
--   the successor case:
--
--     f zero    = f_z
--     f (suc m) = f_s
--
--   Let us again use n¬†+¬†z for the zero case. For the successor case
--   we use ‚â§ùüô¬†¬∑¬†n¬†+¬†s: the argument is not used linearly in the
--   successor case, because it is not used at all, so if n is ùüô, then
--   the result should be at most ‚â§ùüô (not ùüô, because the function is
--   not linear, and not ùüò, because that would amount to an erased
--   match on a natural number).
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†‚â§ùüô, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls, and
--   the argument is used at most once in the successor case
--   (excluding erased uses). Let us again use n¬†+¬†z for the zero
--   case, and ‚â§ùüô¬†¬∑¬†n¬†+¬†s for the successor case.
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†‚â§œâ, then there are no (non-erased) recursive calls. In the
--   successor case the argument is used an unlimited number of times,
--   so we use ‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†n¬†+¬†s. In the zero case we use n¬†+¬†z, as before.
--
-- All of these cases can be expressed in the following way (note that
-- ùüô¬†‚àß¬†ùüò and ùüô¬†‚àß¬†‚â§ùüô are both equal to ‚â§ùüô):
--
--   nr p ùüò z s n = ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n + s) ‚àß (n + z)
--
-- The value of nr¬†p¬†ùüô¬†z¬†s¬†n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†ùüò, then we have linear recursion: the argument is used
--   linearly (n), the successor case can occur an unlimited number of
--   times (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†s), and the zero case occurs once (z).
--
-- * If p is ùüô, ‚â§ùüô or¬†‚â§œâ, then there is recursion (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†s), the
--   argument can be used in each recursive call (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†n), and the
--   zero case occurs once (z).
--
-- We get the following definition:
--
--   nr p ùüô z s n = (ùüô + p) ¬∑ n + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s + z
--
-- The value of nr¬†p¬†‚â§ùüô¬†z¬†s¬†n is defined in the following way:
--
-- * If p¬†=¬†ùüò, then we have affine recursion: the argument is used
--   affinely (‚â§ùüô¬†¬∑¬†n), the successor case can occur an unlimited
--   number of times (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†s), and the zero case occurs at most once
--   (‚â§ùüô¬†¬∑¬†z).
--
-- * If p is ùüô, ‚â§ùüô or¬†‚â§œâ, then there is recursion (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†s), the
--   argument can be used in each recursive call (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†n), and the
--   zero case occurs at most once (‚â§ùüô¬†¬∑¬†z).
--
-- We get the following definition:
--
--   nr p ùüô z s n = (‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z
--
-- Finally we use the following definition for nr¬†p¬†‚â§œâ¬†z¬†s¬†n:
--
--   nr _ ‚â§œâ z s n = ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (n + s + z)
--
-- There is recursion (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†s), in the successor case there can be
-- multiple recursive calls (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†n), and the zero case can occur
-- multiple times (‚â§œâ¬†¬∑¬†z).

nr :
  Linear-or-affine ‚Üí Linear-or-affine ‚Üí
  Linear-or-affine ‚Üí Linear-or-affine ‚Üí Linear-or-affine ‚Üí
  Linear-or-affine
nr p ùüò  z s n = ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n + s) ‚àß (n + z)
nr p ùüô  z s n = (ùüô  + p) ¬∑ n + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s +      z

  lemma‚ÇÇ : ‚àÄ p r ‚Üí nr p r ùüò ùüò ùüò ‚â° ùüò
  lemma‚ÇÇ = Œª where
    ùüò  ùüò  ‚Üí refl
    ùüò  ùüô  ‚Üí refl
    ùüò  ‚â§ùüô ‚Üí refl
    ùüò  ‚â§œâ ‚Üí refl
    ùüô  ùüò  ‚Üí refl
    ùüô  ùüô  ‚Üí refl

    ‚â§ùüô ùüò  ‚Üí refl
    ‚â§ùüô ùüô  ‚Üí refl

    ‚â§ùüô ‚â§œâ ‚Üí refl
    ‚â§œâ ùüò  ‚Üí refl
    ‚â§œâ ùüô  ‚Üí refl
    ‚â§œâ ‚â§ùüô ‚Üí refl
    ‚â§œâ ‚â§œâ ‚Üí refl

-- An nr function can be defined for
-- linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet.

linear-or-affine-has-nr : Has-nr linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet
linear-or-affine-has-nr = record
  { nr          = nr
  ; nr-monotone = Œª {p = p} {r = r} ‚Üí nr-monotone p r
  ; nr-¬∑        = Œª {p = _} {r = r} ‚Üí nr-¬∑ r
  ; nr-+        = Œª {p = _} {r = r} ‚Üí nr-+ r
  ; nr-positive = Œª {p = _} {r = r} ‚Üí nr-ùüò r .proj‚ÇÅ
  ; nr-zero     = Œª {n = _} {p = _} {r = r} ‚Üí nr-zero r _ _ _ _
  ; nr-suc      = Œª {p = _} {r = r} ‚Üí nr-suc r _ _ _ _
  }
  where
  open Semiring-with-meet linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet
    hiding (ùüò; ùüô; _+_; _¬∑_; _‚àß_; _‚â§_)
  open Addition linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet
  open Meet linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet
  open Multiplication linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet
  open PartialOrder linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet

  nr-monotone :
    ‚àÄ p r ‚Üí
    z‚ÇÅ ‚â§ z‚ÇÇ ‚Üí s‚ÇÅ ‚â§ s‚ÇÇ ‚Üí n‚ÇÅ ‚â§ n‚ÇÇ ‚Üí
    nr p r z‚ÇÅ s‚ÇÅ n‚ÇÅ ‚â§ nr p r z‚ÇÇ s‚ÇÇ n‚ÇÇ
  nr-monotone = Œª where
    p ùüò z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ ‚Üí
      ‚àß-monotone (+-monotone (¬∑-monotone ≥ {r = ùüô ‚àß p} n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ) s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ)
        (+-monotone n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ)
    p ùüô z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ ‚Üí
      +-monotone (¬∑-monotone ≥ {r = ùüô + p} n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ)
        (+-monotone (¬∑-monotone ≥ {r = ‚â§œâ} s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ) z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ)
    p ‚â§ùüô z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ ‚Üí
      +-monotone (¬∑-monotone ≥ {r = ‚â§ùüô + p} n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ)
        (+-monotone (¬∑-monotone ≥ {r = ‚â§œâ} s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ)
           (¬∑-monotone ≥ {r = ‚â§ùüô} z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ))
    _ ‚â§œâ z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ ‚Üí
      ¬∑-monotone ≥ {r = ‚â§œâ} (+-monotone n‚ÇÅ‚â§n‚ÇÇ (+-monotone s‚ÇÅ‚â§s‚ÇÇ z‚ÇÅ‚â§z‚ÇÇ))

  nr-¬∑ : ‚àÄ r ‚Üí nr p r z s n ¬∑ q ‚â§ nr p r (z ¬∑ q) (s ¬∑ q) (n ¬∑ q)
  nr-¬∑ {p = p} {z = z} {s = s} {n = n} {q = q} = Œª where
      ùüò ‚Üí begin
        (((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n + s) ‚àß (n + z)) ¬∑ q              ‚â°‚ü® ¬∑-distrib ≥-‚àß _ ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ _ + _) _ ‚ü©
        ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n + s) ¬∑ q ‚àß (n + z) ¬∑ q            ‚â°‚ü® ‚àß-cong (¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ _) _)
                                                            (¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ n _) ‚ü©
        (((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n) ¬∑ q + s ¬∑ q) ‚àß (n ¬∑ q + z ¬∑ q)  ‚â°‚ü® ‚àß-cong ≥ (+-cong ≥ (¬∑-assoc (ùüô ‚àß p) _ _)) ‚ü©
        ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ (n ¬∑ q) + s ¬∑ q) ‚àß (n ¬∑ q + z ¬∑ q)  ‚àé
      ùüô ‚Üí begin
        ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ n + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s + z) ¬∑ q            ‚â°‚ü® ¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ _) _ ‚ü©
        ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ n) ¬∑ q + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s + z) ¬∑ q      ‚â°‚ü® +-congÀ° {x = ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ _) ¬∑ _}
                                                       (¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s) _) ‚ü©
        ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ n) ¬∑ q + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s) ¬∑ q + z ¬∑ q  ‚â°‚ü® +-cong (¬∑-assoc (ùüô + p) _ _)
                                                       (+-cong ≥ (¬∑-assoc ‚â§œâ s _)) ‚ü©
        (ùüô + p) ¬∑ (n ¬∑ q) + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (s ¬∑ q) + z ¬∑ q  ‚àé
      ‚â§ùüô ‚Üí begin
        ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z) ¬∑ q              ‚â°‚ü® ¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ _) _ ‚ü©
        ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n) ¬∑ q + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z) ¬∑ q        ‚â°‚ü® +-congÀ° {x = ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ _) ¬∑ _}
                                                               (¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s) _) ‚ü©
        ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n) ¬∑ q + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s) ¬∑ q + (‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z) ¬∑ q  ‚â°‚ü® +-cong (¬∑-assoc (‚â§ùüô + p) _ _)
                                                               (+-cong (¬∑-assoc ‚â§œâ s _) (¬∑-assoc ‚â§ùüô z _)) ‚ü©
        (‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ (n ¬∑ q) + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (s ¬∑ q) + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ (z ¬∑ q)  ‚àé
      ‚â§œâ ‚Üí begin
        (‚â§œâ ¬∑ (n + s + z)) ¬∑ q        ‚â°‚ü® ¬∑-assoc ‚â§œâ (n + _) _ ‚ü©
        ‚â§œâ ¬∑ ((n + s + z) ¬∑ q)        ‚â°‚ü® ¬∑-congÀ° {x = ‚â§œâ} (¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ n _) ‚ü©
        ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (n ¬∑ q + (s + z) ¬∑ q)    ‚â°‚ü® ¬∑-congÀ° {x = ‚â§œâ} (+-congÀ° {x = n ¬∑ _} (¬∑-distrib ≥-+ _ s _)) ‚ü©
        ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (n ¬∑ q + s ¬∑ q + z ¬∑ q)  ‚àé
    where
    open Tools.Reasoning.PartialOrder ‚â§-poset

  nr-+ :
    ‚àÄ r ‚Üí
    nr p r z‚ÇÅ s‚ÇÅ n‚ÇÅ + nr p r z‚ÇÇ s‚ÇÇ n‚ÇÇ ‚â§
    nr p r (z‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÇ) (s‚ÇÅ + s‚ÇÇ) (n‚ÇÅ + n‚ÇÇ)
  nr-+
    {p = p}
    {z‚ÇÅ = z‚ÇÅ} {s‚ÇÅ = s‚ÇÅ} {n‚ÇÅ = n‚ÇÅ}
    {z‚ÇÇ = z‚ÇÇ} {s‚ÇÇ = s‚ÇÇ} {n‚ÇÇ = n‚ÇÇ} = Œª where
      ùüò ‚Üí begin
        (((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÅ + s‚ÇÅ) ‚àß (n‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÅ)) +
        (((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÇ + s‚ÇÇ) ‚àß (n‚ÇÇ + z‚ÇÇ))                            ‚â§‚ü® +-sub-interchangeable-‚àß ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ _ + _) _ _ _ ‚ü©

        (((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÅ + s‚ÇÅ) + ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÇ + s‚ÇÇ)) ‚àß
        ((n‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÅ) + (n‚ÇÇ + z‚ÇÇ))                                      ‚â°‚ü® ‚àß-cong (+-sub-interchangeable-+ ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ _) _ _ _)
                                                                          (+-sub-interchangeable-+ n‚ÇÅ _ _ _) ‚ü©
        (((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÅ + (ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÇ) + (s‚ÇÅ + s‚ÇÇ)) ‚àß
        ((n‚ÇÅ + n‚ÇÇ) + (z‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÇ))                                      ‚â°Àò‚ü® ‚àß-cong ≥ (+-cong ≥ (¬∑-distribÀ°-+ (ùüô ‚àß p) _ _)) ‚ü©

        ((ùüô ‚àß p) ¬∑ (n‚ÇÅ + n‚ÇÇ) + (s‚ÇÅ + s‚ÇÇ)) ‚àß ((n‚ÇÅ + n‚ÇÇ) + (z‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÇ))  ‚àé
      ùüô ‚Üí begin
        ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÅ + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÅ) + ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÇ + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÇ + z‚ÇÇ)    ‚â°‚ü® +-sub-interchangeable-+ ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ _) _ _ _ ‚ü©
        ((ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÅ + (ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÇ) + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÅ) + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÇ + z‚ÇÇ)  ‚â°‚ü® +-cong (sym (¬∑-distribÀ°-+ (ùüô + p) _ _))
                                                                              (+-sub-interchangeable-+ (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÅ) _ _ _) ‚ü©
        (ùüô + p) ¬∑ (n‚ÇÅ + n‚ÇÇ) + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÅ + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÇ) + (z‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÇ)            ‚â°Àò‚ü® +-congÀ° {x = (ùüô + p) ¬∑ _}
                                                                               (+-cong ≥ (¬∑-distribÀ°-+ ‚â§œâ s‚ÇÅ _)) ‚ü©
        (ùüô + p) ¬∑ (n‚ÇÅ + n‚ÇÇ) + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ (s‚ÇÅ + s‚ÇÇ) + (z‚ÇÅ + z‚ÇÇ)                 ‚àé
      ‚â§ùüô ‚Üí begin
        ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÅ + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÅ + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z‚ÇÅ) +
        ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÇ + ‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÇ + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z‚ÇÇ)                               ‚â°‚ü® +-sub-interchangeable-+ ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ _) _ _ _ ‚ü©

        ((‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÅ + (‚â§ùüô + p) ¬∑ n‚ÇÇ) +
        (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÅ + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z‚ÇÅ) + (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÇ + ‚â§ùüô ¬∑ z‚ÇÇ)                         ‚â°‚ü® +-cong (sym (¬∑-distribÀ°-+ (‚â§ùüô + p) _ _))
                                                                               (+-sub-interchangeable-+ (‚â§œâ ¬∑ s‚ÇÅ) _ _ _) ‚ü©

  nr-suc : ‚àÄ r p z s n ‚Üí nr p r z s n ‚â§ s + p ¬∑ n + r ¬∑ nr p r z s n

opaque

  -- The nr-function defined above is factoring

  linear-or-affine-has-factoring-nr :
    Is-factoring-nr linear-or-affine-has-nr
  linear-or-affine-has-factoring-nr = record
    { nr‚ÇÇ = nr‚ÇÇ
    ; nr‚ÇÇ‚â¢ùüò = Œª {p} {r} ‚Üí ùüô‚àßp‚â¢ùüò (r + p)
    ; nr-factoring = Œª {p} {r} {z} {s} {n} ‚Üí nr-factoring p r z s n
    }
    where
    open Semiring-with-meet linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet
      hiding (ùüò; ùüô; _+_; _¬∑_; _‚àß_; _‚â§_)

    nr‚ÇÇ : Op‚ÇÇ Linear-or-affine
    nr‚ÇÇ p r = ùüô ‚àß (r + p)

    ùüô‚àß‚â§ùüô+p‚â°‚â§1+p : ‚àÄ p ‚Üí ùüô ‚àß (‚â§ùüô + p) ‚â° ‚â§ùüô + p
    ùüô‚àß‚â§ùüô+p‚â°‚â§1+p ùüò = refl
    ùüô‚àß‚â§ùüô+p‚â°‚â§1+p ùüô = refl
    ùüô‚àß‚â§ùüô+p‚â°‚â§1+p ‚â§ùüô = refl
    ùüô‚àß‚â§ùüô+p‚â°‚â§1+p ‚â§œâ = refl

    ùüô‚àßùüô+p‚â°1+p : ‚àÄ p ‚Üí ùüô ‚àß (ùüô + p) ‚â° ùüô + p
    ùüô‚àßùüô+p‚â°1+p ùüò = refl
    ùüô‚àßùüô+p‚â°1+p ùüô = refl
    ùüô‚àßùüô+p‚â°1+p ‚â§ùüô = refl
    ùüô‚àßùüô+p‚â°1+p ‚â§œâ = refl

    lemma : ‚àÄ p z s n ‚Üí p ‚â¢ ùüò
          ‚Üí (p ¬∑ n + s) ‚àß (n + z) ‚â° p ¬∑ n + s ‚àß z
    lemma ùüò z s n p‚â¢ùüò = ‚ä•-elim (p‚â¢ùüò refl)
    lemma ùüô z s n p‚â¢ùüò rewrite ¬∑-identityÀ° n =
      sym (+-distribÀ°-‚àß n s z)
    lemma ‚â§ùüô z s ùüò p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ùüò ùüò ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ùüô ùüò ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ‚â§ùüô ùüò ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ‚â§œâ ùüò ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ùüò ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ùüô ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ‚â§ùüô ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ‚â§œâ ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ùüò ‚â§ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ùüô ‚â§ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ‚â§ùüô ‚â§ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô ‚â§œâ ‚â§ùüô ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô z ‚â§œâ ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§ùüô z s ‚â§ùüô p‚â¢ùüò = sym (+-distribÀ°-‚àß ‚â§ùüô s z)
    lemma ‚â§ùüô z s ‚â§œâ p‚â¢ùüò = sym (+-distribÀ°-‚àß ‚â§œâ s z)
    lemma ‚â§œâ z s ùüò p‚â¢ùüò = refl
    lemma ‚â§œâ z s ùüô p‚â¢ùüò rewrite ‚â§œâ+ s rewrite ‚â§œâ+ (s ‚àß z) = refl
    lemma ‚â§œâ z s ‚â§ùüô p‚â¢ùüò rewrite ‚â§œâ+ s rewrite ‚â§œâ+ (s ‚àß z) = refl
    lemma ‚â§œâ z s ‚â§œâ p‚â¢ùüò = sym (+-distribÀ°-‚àß ‚â§œâ s z)

    nr-factoring : (p r z s n : Linear-or-affine)
                 ‚Üí nr p r z s n ‚â° nr‚ÇÇ p r ¬∑ n + nr p r z s ùüò
    nr-factoring p ùüò z s n rewrite ¬∑-zero ≥ (ùüô ‚àß p) =
      lemma (ùüô ‚àß p) z s n (ùüô‚àßp‚â¢ùüò p)
    nr-factoring p ùüô z s n rewrite ¬∑-zero ≥ (ùüô + p) =
      +-cong ≥ (¬∑-cong ≥ (sym (ùüô‚àßùüô+p‚â°1+p p)))
    nr-factoring p ‚â§ùüô z s n rewrite ¬∑-zero ≥ (‚â§ùüô + p) =
      +-cong ≥ (¬∑-cong ≥ (sym (ùüô‚àß‚â§ùüô+p‚â°‚â§1+p p)))
    nr-factoring p ‚â§œâ z s n rewrite ‚â§œâ+ p = ¬∑-distribÀ°-+ œâ n (s + z)

opaque

  -- The nr function returns results that are at least as large as those
  -- of any other factoring nr function for linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet.

  nr-greatest-factoring :
    (has-nr : Has-nr linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet)

        ‚â§œâ                            ‚àé
      p r z ‚â§œâ n ‚Üí lemma $ begin
        nr‚Ä≤ p r z ‚â§œâ n                  ‚â§‚ü® nr-suc ‚ü©

-- Instances of Full-reduction-assumptions

-- Instances of Type-restrictions and Usage-restrictions are suitable
-- for the full reduction theorem if
-- * whenever UnitÀ¢-allowed holds, then StarÀ¢-sink holds,
-- * Unit ∑-allowed and Unit ∑-Œ∑ do not both hold,
-- * Œ£À¢-allowed¬†ùüò¬†p does not hold,
-- * Œ£À¢-allowed¬†‚â§ùüô¬†p does not hold, and
-- * Œ£À¢-allowed¬†‚â§œâ¬†p does not hold.

Suitable-for-full-reduction :
  ‚àÄ variant ‚Üí
  Type-restrictions (linear-or-affine variant) ‚Üí
  Usage-restrictions (linear-or-affine variant) ‚Üí
  Set
Suitable-for-full-reduction variant rs us =
  (UnitÀ¢-allowed ‚Üí StarÀ¢-sink) √ó
  (Unit ∑-allowed ‚Üí ¬¨ Unit ∑-Œ∑) √ó
  (‚àÄ p ‚Üí ¬¨ Œ£À¢-allowed ùüò p) √ó
  (‚àÄ p ‚Üí ¬¨ Œ£À¢-allowed ‚â§ùüô p) √ó
  (‚àÄ p ‚Üí ¬¨ Œ£À¢-allowed ‚â§œâ p)
  where
  open Type-restrictions  rs
  open Usage-restrictions us

-- Given an instance of Type-restrictions¬†(linear-or-affine¬†variant)
-- one can create a "suitable" instance.

suitable-for-full-reduction :
  Type-restrictions (linear-or-affine variant) ‚Üí
  ‚àÉ Œª rs ‚Üí Suitable-for-full-reduction variant rs urs
suitable-for-full-reduction {urs} rs =
    record rs
      { Unit-allowed = Œª where
          ùï§ ‚Üí UnitÀ¢-allowed √ó StarÀ¢-sink
          ùï® ‚Üí Unit ∑-allowed √ó ¬¨ Unit ∑-Œ∑
      ; Œ†Œ£-allowed   = Œª b p q ‚Üí
          Œ†Œ£-allowed b p q √ó (b ‚â° BMŒ£ ùï§ ‚Üí p ‚â° ùüô)
      ; []-cong-allowed = Œª where
          ùï§ ‚Üí ‚ä•
          ùï® ‚Üí []-cong ∑-allowed √ó ¬¨ Unit ∑-Œ∑
      ; []-cong‚ÜíErased = Œª where
          {s = ùï§} ()
          {s = ùï®} (ok , no-Œ∑) ‚Üí
            case []-cong‚ÜíErased ok of Œª
              (ok‚ÇÅ , ok‚ÇÇ) ‚Üí
            (ok‚ÇÅ , no-Œ∑) , ok‚ÇÇ , (Œª ())
      ; []-cong‚Üí¬¨Trivial = Œª where
          {s = ùï§} ()
          {s = ùï®}    ‚Üí []-cong‚Üí¬¨Trivial ‚àò‚Üí proj‚ÇÅ
      }
  , proj‚ÇÇ
  , proj‚ÇÇ
  , (Œª _ ‚Üí ((Œª ()) ‚àò‚Üí (_$ PE.refl)) ‚àò‚Üí proj‚ÇÇ)
  , (Œª _ ‚Üí ((Œª ()) ‚àò‚Üí (_$ PE.refl)) ‚àò‚Üí proj‚ÇÇ)
  , (Œª _ ‚Üí ((Œª ()) ‚àò‚Üí (_$ PE.refl)) ‚àò‚Üí proj‚ÇÇ)
  where
  open Type-restrictions rs
  open Usage-restrictions urs

-- The full reduction assumptions hold for any instance of
-- linear-or-affine and any "suitable" Type-restrictions and
-- Usage-restrictions.

full-reduction-assumptions :
  Suitable-for-full-reduction variant trs urs ‚Üí
  Full-reduction-assumptions trs urs
full-reduction-assumptions (sink , no-Œ∑ , ¬¨ùüò , ¬¨‚â§ùüô , ¬¨‚â§œâ) = record
  { sink‚äéùüô‚â§ùüò = Œª where
      {s = ùï§} ok _         ‚Üí inj‚ÇÅ (refl , sink ok)
      {s = ùï®} _  (inj‚ÇÅ ())
      {s = ùï®} ok (inj‚ÇÇ Œ∑)  ‚Üí ‚ä•-elim (no-Œ∑ ok Œ∑)
  ; ‚â°ùüô‚äéùüô‚â§ùüò = Œª where
      {p = ùüò}  ok ‚Üí ‚ä•-elim (¬¨ùüò _ ok)
      {p = ‚â§ùüô} ok ‚Üí ‚ä•-elim (¬¨‚â§ùüô _ ok)
      {p = ‚â§œâ} ok ‚Üí ‚ä•-elim (¬¨‚â§œâ _ ok)
      {p = ùüô}  _  ‚Üí inj‚ÇÅ refl
  }

-- Type and usage restrictions that satisfy the full reduction
-- assumptions are "suitable".

full-reduction-assumptions-suitable :
  Full-reduction-assumptions trs urs ‚Üí
  Suitable-for-full-reduction variant trs urs
full-reduction-assumptions-suitable {urs = urs} as =
     (Œª ok ‚Üí case sink‚äéùüô‚â§ùüò ok (inj‚ÇÅ refl) of Œª where
        (inj‚ÇÅ (_ , sink)) ‚Üí sink
        (inj‚ÇÇ ()))
   , (Œª ok Œ∑ ‚Üí case sink‚äéùüô‚â§ùüò ok (inj‚ÇÇ Œ∑) of Œª where
        (inj‚ÇÅ (() , _))
        (inj‚ÇÇ ()))
   , (Œª p Œ£-ok ‚Üí case ‚â°ùüô‚äéùüô‚â§ùüò Œ£-ok of Œª where
        (inj‚ÇÅ ())
        (inj‚ÇÇ (_ , _ , ())))
   , (Œª p Œ£-ok ‚Üí case ‚â°ùüô‚äéùüô‚â§ùüò Œ£-ok of Œª where
        (inj‚ÇÅ ())
        (inj‚ÇÇ (() , _)))
   , Œª p Œ£-ok ‚Üí case ‚â°ùüô‚äéùüô‚â§ùüò Œ£-ok of Œª where
        (inj‚ÇÅ ())
        (inj‚ÇÇ (() , _))
  where
  open Full-reduction-assumptions as
  open Usage-restrictions urs

opaque

  -- The semiring supports subtraction with
  --   ‚â§œâ - p ‚â° ‚â§œâ for all p
  --   p - ùüò ‚â° p for all p
  --   ùüô - ùüô ‚â° ùüò
  --   ‚â§ùüô - ‚â§ùüô ‚â° ùüò
  --   ‚â§ùüô - ùüô ‚â° ùüò
  -- and not defined otherwise

  supports-subtraction : Supports-subtraction
  supports-subtraction {p} {(‚â§œâ)} {r} x =
    case p-œâ‚â∞ {q = r} x of Œª {
      refl ‚Üí
    ‚â§œâ , œâ-p‚â°œâ ‚â§œâ }
  supports-subtraction {p} {(ùüò)} {r} x =
    p , p-ùüò‚â°p
  supports-subtraction {(‚â§œâ)} {q} _ =

      (refl , refl) ‚Üí
    ùüò , p-ùüò‚â°p }

    ùüò , p-p‚â§ùüò ,
    Œª where
      ùüò  _  ‚Üí refl
      ùüô  ()
      ‚â§ùüô ()
      ‚â§œâ ()
  supports-subtraction {(‚â§ùüô)} {(ùüô)} x =
    ùüò , ‚â§ùüô-ùüô‚â°ùüò
  supports-subtraction {(‚â§ùüô)} {(‚â§ùüô)} x =
    ùüò , p-p‚â§ùüò ,
    Œª where
      ùüò  _  ‚Üí refl
      ùüô  ()
      ‚â§ùüô ()
      ‚â§œâ ()
  supports-subtraction {(ùüô)} {(‚â§ùüô)} {r} x =
    ‚ä•-elim (ùüô-‚â§ùüô‚â∞ {p = r} x)

-- An alternative definition of the subtraction relation with
--   ‚â§œâ - p ‚â° ‚â§œâ for all p
--   p - ùüò ‚â° p for all p
--   ùüô - ùüô ‚â° ùüò
--   ‚â§ùüô - ‚â§ùüô ‚â° ùüò
--   ‚â§ùüô - ùüô ‚â° ùüò
-- and not defined otherwise

data _-_‚â°‚Ä≤_ : (p q r : Linear-or-affine) ‚Üí Set where
  œâ-p‚â°‚Ä≤œâ : ‚â§œâ - p ‚â°‚Ä≤ ‚â§œâ
  p-ùüò‚â°‚Ä≤p : p - ùüò ‚â°‚Ä≤ p
  ùüô-ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò : ùüô - ùüô ‚â°‚Ä≤ ùüò
  ‚â§ùüô-‚â§ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò : ‚â§ùüô - ‚â§ùüô ‚â°‚Ä≤ ùüò
  ‚â§ùüô-ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò : ‚â§ùüô - ùüô ‚â°‚Ä≤ ùüò

opaque

  -- The two subtraction relations are equivalent.

  -‚â°‚Üî-‚â°‚Ä≤ : ‚àÄ p q r ‚Üí (p - q ‚â° r) ‚áî (p - q ‚â°‚Ä≤ r)
  -‚â°‚Üî-‚â°‚Ä≤ p q r = left p q r , right
    where
    left : ‚àÄ p q r ‚Üí p - q ‚â° r ‚Üí p - q ‚â°‚Ä≤ r
    left ‚â§œâ q r p-q‚â°r =
      case -‚â°-functional {q = q} p-q‚â°r (œâ-p‚â°œâ q) of Œª {
        refl ‚Üí
      œâ-p‚â°‚Ä≤œâ }
    left p ùüò r p-q‚â°r =
      case -‚â°-functional p-q‚â°r p-ùüò‚â°p of Œª {
        refl ‚Üí
      p-ùüò‚â°‚Ä≤p }
    left ùüò q r p-q‚â°r =
      case ùüò-p‚â°q p-q‚â°r of Œª {
        (refl , refl) ‚Üí
      p-ùüò‚â°‚Ä≤p}
    left ùüô ùüô r p-q‚â°r =
      case -‚â°-functional p-q‚â°r ùüô-ùüô‚â°ùüò of Œª {
        refl ‚Üí
      ùüô-ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò }
    left ‚â§ùüô ‚â§ùüô r p-q‚â°r =
      case -‚â°-functional p-q‚â°r ‚â§ùüô-‚â§ùüô‚â°ùüò of Œª {
        refl ‚Üí
      ‚â§ùüô-‚â§ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò }
    left ‚â§ùüô ùüô r p-q‚â°r =
      case -‚â°-functional p-q‚â°r ‚â§ùüô-ùüô‚â°ùüò of Œª {
        refl ‚Üí
      ‚â§ùüô-ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò }
    left ùüô ‚â§ùüô r p-q‚â°r =
      ‚ä•-elim (ùüô-‚â§ùüô‚â¢ {r} p-q‚â°r)
    left ùüô ‚â§œâ r p-q‚â°r =
      case p-œâ‚â¢ p-q‚â°r of Œª ()
    left ‚â§ùüô ‚â§œâ r p-q‚â°r =
      case p-œâ‚â¢ p-q‚â°r of Œª ()
    right : p - q ‚â°‚Ä≤ r ‚Üí p - q ‚â° r
    right œâ-p‚â°‚Ä≤œâ = œâ-p‚â°œâ p
    right p-ùüò‚â°‚Ä≤p = p-ùüò‚â°p
    right ùüô-ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò = ùüô-ùüô‚â°ùüò
    right ‚â§ùüô-‚â§ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò = ‚â§ùüô-‚â§ùüô‚â°ùüò
    right ‚â§ùüô-ùüô‚â°‚Ä≤ùüò = ‚â§ùüô-ùüô‚â°ùüò

-- Properties of greatest lower bounds

opaque

  -- nr¬†ùüò¬†r¬†z¬†s¬†ùüò is the greatest lower bound of nr·µ¢¬†r¬†z¬†s.

  nr-nr·µ¢-GLB :
    let ùïÑ = linear-or-affine-semiring-with-meet in
      ‚àÄ r ‚Üí Semiring-with-meet.Greatest-lower-bound
              ùïÑ (nr ùüò r z s ùüò) (Semiring-with-meet.nr·µ¢ ùïÑ r z s)
  nr-nr·µ¢-GLB = Œª where

            (‚àß-comm _ _))) nr·µ¢-ùüò-GLB

      ‚â§œâ ‚Üí lemma-œâ _ _

      hiding (ùüò; ùüô; œâ; _‚àß_; _¬∑_; _+_)

    lemma‚Ä≤ : ‚àÄ {z} i ‚Üí nr·µ¢ ùüô z ùüò i ‚â° z

      Semiring-with-meet.Greatest-lower-bound

opaque

    { +-GLBÀ° = Œª {_} {_} {q} ‚Üí +-GLBÀ° {q = q}
